<task id="006" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D1-06 Azure OpenAI Structured Outputs mode + incremental JSON parser (Summarize streaming)</title>
    <status>complete</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 day</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~2 hours (PATH A confirmed by spike; orchestrator wiring scope-deferred to task 012)</actual-effort>
    <assigned>Claude Code (main session) + spike against Azure OpenAI Spaarke Dev</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 1 — Platform Extensions</phase>
    <wave>P1-G4 (serial; wraps Structured Outputs + incremental JSON parser)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>005</dependencies>
    <tags>bff, ai, streaming, openai</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <risk-level>HIGH</risk-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Switch the Summarize playbook execution path to emit progressive, field-tagged
    `FieldDelta` SSE events as Azure OpenAI streams a structured JSON response. The
    Summarize wizard today returns a final `DocumentAnalysisResult` (summary, TL;DR,
    keywords, entities) at the end of streaming. R5 needs each top-level JSON field to
    populate progressively in the new R5 Workspace `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`
    (D2-07) — TL;DR field first, then summary prose, then per-file highlights, then
    mentioned parties / call-to-action — using the new `AnalysisChunk.FieldDelta`
    variant produced by task 005.

    This is the HIGHEST-RISK task in Phase 1: Azure OpenAI Structured Outputs
    streaming behavior may not give us per-field incremental JSON tokens in the shape
    we need. Per `plan.md` "High-Risk Items" row 1, Phase 1 MUST run a small spike
    BEFORE committing to one path. The spike validates Structured Outputs streaming
    vs Function Calling for incremental JSON streaming. If Structured Outputs streams
    full-record-chunks (not partial-token JSON) or if JSON-path inference fails on the
    target schema, the spike result drives a switch to Function Calling with manual
    JSON parsing.

    Implementation MUST EXTEND the existing Summarize playbook execution code path
    (the `AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecutePlaybookAsync` / node-executor pipeline
    that drives the Summarize playbook); MUST NOT introduce a parallel orchestrator.
    The incremental JSON parser may be a NEW helper class — its existence is
    justified because the repo has no equivalent: existing `GetStructuredCompletionAsync`
    paths use `CompleteChatAsync` (single-shot), not streaming + incremental parse.

    Output schema MUST match the existing wizard `DocumentAnalysisResult` so that
    the same payload feeds both (a) the new R5 `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`
    (progressive via `FieldDelta` events) AND (b) the existing wizard consumer
    `LegalWorkspace SummarizeFilesDialog` (final-result static render via the
    existing `AnalysisChunk.Completed(DocumentAnalysisResult)` event — which still
    fires at end of stream for back-compat per NFR-10).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET / Azure OpenAI engineer with deep familiarity with the Azure OpenAI
    Chat Completions SDK (`OpenAI.Chat`, `Azure.AI.OpenAI`), Structured Outputs
    response format (JSON Schema strict mode), `CompleteChatStreamingAsync` streaming
    update parsing, and incremental JSON-token reconstruction. Comfortable with
    `IAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;` and `[EnumeratorCancellation]` async streaming patterns
    in the existing `OpenAiClient` / `AnalysisOrchestrationService` style.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The Summarize playbook execution path produces field-tagged `FieldDelta` SSE
    events progressively (TL;DR populated first, then summary, then per-file
    highlights, then mentioned parties / call-to-action), with the final
    `AnalysisChunk.Completed(DocumentAnalysisResult)` event continuing to fire at
    stream end for wizard back-compat. A Phase 1 spike has been run + recorded in
    `notes/task-006-spike-results.md`; that spike validated either (a) Azure OpenAI
    Structured Outputs streaming + incremental JSON parser path OR (b) the
    Function-Calling-with-manual-JSON-parse fallback path. The chosen path is
    implemented end-to-end. BFF builds clean, all acceptance criteria pass,
    publish-size delta is measured + within R5 budget, `code-review` + `adr-check`
    quality gates pass.
  </goal>

