  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 spec FR-02">SSE token-streamed structured summary in Workspace pane. Summary output MUST stream progressively via `FieldDelta` SSE events as Azure OpenAI emits tokens; structured fields (TL;DR, summary, per-file highlights, mentioned parties, call-to-action) MUST populate progressively. NOT a final-result plop.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 spec FR-13">`StructuredOutputStreamWidget` consumes `FieldDelta` events progressively. R5 Workspace D2-07 widget depends on this task's event emission order + shape.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 spec NFR-10">Back-compat for AnalysisChunk SSE protocol. The new `FieldDelta` variant is ADDITIVE; existing wizard consumers (LegalWorkspace `SummarizeFilesDialog` via `streamSummarize()`) MUST continue to function — they ignore unknown event types and continue to receive the final `AnalysisChunk.Completed(DocumentAnalysisResult)` event at stream end.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (Reuse mandate)">MUST extend the existing Summarize playbook execution code path (`AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecutePlaybookAsync` + the Summarize tool/node pipeline). MUST NOT introduce a parallel orchestrator. Tool registration for `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` is task 015 — out of scope here.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (Reuse exception justification)">The incremental JSON parser MAY be a new helper class. Justification: the existing `OpenAiClient.GetStructuredCompletionAsync&lt;T&gt;` / `GetStructuredCompletionRawAsync` use `CompleteChatAsync` (single-shot) and return only the final JSON string. `StreamCompletionAsync` exists but is plain-text streaming — no incremental JSON-path tagging. R5 needs the union: streaming + incremental JSON path inference. Record this justification in the PR design notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (NO new feature flags)">R5 introduces NO new feature flags per ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline. The new Structured-Outputs streaming path replaces (or wraps) the existing non-streaming structured-output path unconditionally. No `if (FeatureFlag.X)` branching at the service layer.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.3 (DI discipline)">If a new helper service (incremental JSON parser) needs DI registration, register it INSIDE `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` feature module per ADR-010. ZERO new top-level `services.AddXxx()` lines in `Program.cs`. Concrete classes by default; no interface unless an existing test seam demands it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 + ADR-029 (BFF publish-size)">Per-task verification mandatory. Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/` AFTER implementation. Measure compressed output. Report absolute size + delta vs prior baseline in task notes. Current baseline ~45.65 MB; R5 budget ≤ +1 MB total across R5; this task's individual delta should approach 0 MB if no new NuGet packages are added. If Azure OpenAI / Structured Outputs requires a package upgrade, measure carefully and flag.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 (BFF-only AI placement)">AI orchestration stays in BFF. No new project / library carved out for the JSON parser. Helper class lives alongside `OpenAiClient` in `Services/Ai/` (suggested folder: `Services/Ai/Streaming/`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014 (tenant isolation)">N/A directly for this task — task does not introduce new index documents. Confirm no impact in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019 (ProblemDetails)">Any new error surface (e.g., JSON parse failure mid-stream) maps to ProblemDetails with a stable `errorCode` extension if it propagates to an endpoint. Mid-stream parse failure should emit an `AnalysisChunk.FromError(...)` event, NOT crash the stream.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 + CVE policy">No new HIGH-severity CVEs from `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`. If Structured Outputs spike reveals a need for a newer Azure.AI.OpenAI / OpenAI SDK package, verify CVE-clean before adopting.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 NFR-01 (Latency)">SSE TTFB &lt; 500ms per ADR-013. Field-level emissions should NOT block waiting for full-field completion before first emission — the FIRST `FieldDelta` event for a field SHOULD fire as soon as the JSON parser recognizes the field boundary opening (`"tldr":`), with subsequent intra-field deltas optional but preferred.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spike requirement (plan.md High-Risk Items row 1)">Before committing to Structured Outputs, run a small spike validating: (a) Azure OpenAI Structured Outputs streams partial JSON tokens (not chunked full-record); (b) chosen JSON-path inference works for the Summarize schema. If spike fails, fallback path is Function Calling with manual JSON parsing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="output schema parity">Final `DocumentAnalysisResult` shape (summary, tldr, keywords, entities, emailMetadata, parsedSuccessfully, rawResponse) MUST be preserved end-to-stream so D2-07 `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` can render either streaming or static-restored output, and the existing wizard consumer continues to function unchanged. If R5 wants additional fields (per-file highlights, mentioned parties, call-to-action), they are added ADDITIVELY to `DocumentAnalysisResult` — but that is a SEPARATE concern; do not block this task on schema additions if not strictly needed for Phase 1. Document any deferred additions in task notes for task 010 (action seed).</constraint>
    <constraint source="back-compat (wizard consumer)">The wizard consumer (`LegalWorkspace SummarizeFilesDialog` → `streamSummarize()` in `summarizeService.ts`) MUST continue to render correctly. Verify by reading the consumer code + confirming it ignores `Type = "delta"` events and waits for `Type = "complete"`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

